leads.lead_text: Bracts rhombic to almost orbicular, 1.5–3 mm wide; corolla mostly purple; abaxial lamina of mature leaves largely (sometimes wholly) obscured by septate hairs 1 mm long or more, usually with some glandular hairs intermixed; leaves strongly aromatic

Bracts elliptic to ovate, to 1–1.3 mm wide; corolla usually mostly white or pale lilac; abaxial lamina of mature leaves generally obvious beneath rather sparse septate hairs under 1 mm long, without intermixed glandular hairs; leaves odourless or nearly so
